messages.content: Gemi was looking
"You found anything yet?" Thought-Shale starts to climb up a tree. "Rainforests are cool and all-" she slides down slightly. "But they're difficult to navigate."
Gemi shook her head
Thought-Shale claws her way up the tree. "I can see *something*!" she yells down. "That way!"
Gemi follows her voice
Thought-Shale heads through the canopy because that's fun. She reaches a small pit with cracks zig-zagging out of it everywhere.
"Well. That's something.." Even Thought-Shale is daunted. "We can fix this, though! Let's jump in it."
"How?!"
"I don't know! I assume there'll be something to punch!" Thought-Shale yells, and jumps in the pit without another word.
Gemi follows
Beneath there is a cloud of... grayness. "Looks like that's your manifestation of Imposter syndrome.... if we disperse this, I *think* it might help and give us the ability to fill in the cracks."
"Can we really fight this thing?"
"Gemi it's a cloud. How hard can it be?" ....The cloud rushes in to fill the outline of a very distinctly Gemi-shaped silhouette. "Ah."
Words started echoing. Words gemi had heard in her past. Including what Morise had told her
"Gemi." Thought-Shale grips her fiance's hand. "I'll let you throw the first punch." The Gemi-Figure is approaching, slowly.
Gemi instinctively tries to release her stand ... Whoops. She uses her fists
Shale grins. "Let's do this." The Gemi-Figure is rocked backwards by Gemi's punches.
Gemi continues fighting trying to remain confident
Suddenly she's hallucinating
Visions of war and dead muns
"Gemi. It's not real." Shale is there, trying to anchor her to reality. Her fists go straight through the Gemi-Figure like it's not even there. "Gemi, we need you to fight this thing..."
Gemi is trying but keeps doubting herself
Shale backs away, very slowly, from the figure. "I can't touch it..."
"Why?"
"How would I know?" The figure darts forward and grabs Shale around the throat. "It can touch me, apparently-" Shale tries her best to remain calm, but her leg is trembling...
Gemi immediately lunges at not-gemi and begins furiously attacking it.
Not-Gemi is forced back, each area where it's punched disappearing. Shale drops, rubbing her throat. "I'll cheer from the sidelines.."
Gemi continues fighting
Not-Gemi is reduced to a small pile of shadows... After a few seconds, the shards reform into a vial. Shale stands up.
"What happened?"
"I think you killed it..." Shale frowns. "Thank you for saving me..." she picks up the vial. "Try pouring it on one of the cracks, it might help. Or you could drink it. I don't know."
She pours it on one of the cracks. She doesn't trust it enough to drink it
The crack (but only that one) rumbles, and seals up. "Well. There we go..." Shale sits down. "It's beautiful here, isn't it? Beautiful mind... Beautiful mindscape."
Gemi nods.
"Do you believe me now? You're an inherently good person; you saved my life at the drop of a hat."
"but...all those other muns..."
"Will not die. You and I are going to protect them. Besides, Morise was never going to retreat."
"She said she called it off because of ME."
"Oh please. They said it to hurt you. They're a bastard and you shouldn't believe anything they say."
Gemi just...hugged Shale
"Should we get out now?"
"If you want." Shale smiles, and vanishes in a burst of light.
Gemi was trying to relax
"You know, Gemi..." a voice whispered "This happens so wearily often. Are you sure you're not just faking your 'mental disorder' for attention?"

"No, I'm not taking this mistreatment! I have imposter syndrome and I should stop getting into trouble!"
"Why didn't you try to fight Pucci mun? Did you want to be the damsel in distress?"
"Ew, no! I was hurt and confused after trying to fight Morise!"
"Stop trying to defend yourself."
"Im not, I'm just saying what happened!"
"Everyone wants me to start accepting myself....the first step will definitely be a hard one..."
*but it'll be worth it, Gemi.*
"yeah...it'll be worth it."
Her mindscape is nice and relaxing
She's eating a sammich under the shade of a tree
And now there's an earthquake and fire going on in this rainforest
And now she's standing in the ruins of what was once a vibrant forest
"...it's always gonna be like this forever." She sighed and sat down
"I'm not getting better..."
*Not true...*
Gemi turns to see a glowing orb
"Ah, what do YOU know?"
*I am your subconscious. I know more than what you do.*
"...What are you talking about?"
*I'm talking about...*
It played multiple clips of recent days from when Gemi was mentally strong

"Well those are all for nothing when I fall back down!"
*You always catch yourself and climb back up.*
"BUT I'M NOT GETTING BETTER!"
*Nobody said the path to progress would be smooth. After each relapse, you grow a little stronger. Even for just having survived it.*
"I'm not any better than where I started out!"
*You aren't getting like this nearly as frequently as you used to. Relapses will happen*
"Why does my subconscious sound like a completely different person?!"
It plays another montage. Every bit of encouragement her fiances, Polaris, and others have ever given her
*those words are immortalized somewhere inside you. You need to process them, Gemi. You ARE strong. Even without your stand.*
Gemi is silent
Some greenery grows back
*Gemi, you're technically right. You DO need to help yourself. But not in the way you think. It's ok to need help from others. What you gotta do is process their words. Watch these clips a bit more.*
Gemi watches as the orb plays kindness she's received
She focuses
Slowly, her mindscape rainforest begins to regrow
Gemi is processing these words
Processing how much she means to everyone else
Processing how she's ignored how amazing she is
//brb gonna reread some of shale's speeches
//idk if polaris ever gave her words of encouragement but i feel like it's a thing he did
Gemi was
feeling really good
but suddenly felt a shiver down her spine
her mindscape began to tilt
She was just
sitting down
She saw another her in the distance
digging
She shut her eyes
"I...don't want to look..."
She opened her eyes to look at arms
still cracks from that day
she frowned
"This wouldn't have happened if I wasn't weak..."
*Keep your head up, Gemi. You've got a wedding soon.*
Gemi is here
and
she's straight up not having a good time
Gemi's mindscape has been much more lively and bright for a while
but now it was overcast
the animals nowhere to be found
She just
walks up to a nearby tree
and starts punching it
before laying down in the fetal position and crying
*maybe if you had gotten closer to him you could've prevented this*
*Malachite was as close to Polaris as one could get-*
*Is that so? They must not have been close if Polaris left him*
